  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribution to ACT Armenia Appeal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid&apos;s contribution will contribute to funding for the Armenia Inter-Church Charitable Round Table Foundation (ART) to deliver the following activities:

Shelter: 50 flats will be purchased to function as permanent shelters for the most vulnerable families.

Livelihoods: 66 individuals will receive vocational training in IT, hairdressing, cookery and craft.

Psychosocial support:  250 refugees (adults and children) will participate in private and group psychosocial sessions. Workshops on stress management and building self-esteem will be available for adults and art therapy will be available for children. 

Community resilience: Armenian, Russian and English Language training courses will be organized by ART for 45 refugees and community integration will be promoted through cultural and awareness raising activities such as participating at exhibitions and events organized by different local and international organisations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This multi-sectoral approach will promote integration and cohesion between refugee and host communities through permanent shelter provision and economic, emotional, linguistic and social support which will enable individuals to  build new lives following conflict and displacement.</narrative>
  </description>
